Azure Alerts notify users when specific conditions are met, such as high CPU usage or service downtime. Action groups define how notifications are sent.

For example, an alert can trigger an email or SMS when a server’s CPU usage exceeds 90%.

A real-life use case is incident management. IT teams receive alerts and respond quickly to issues.

Another example is automated scaling, where alerts trigger scripts to scale resources.

Alerts ensure proactive monitoring and quick response to problems.
